author: bmitchell
msg: AXIS2C-933: Fix guththila parser to always detect EOF and end the parse, not
Fix detection of malloc failure in the buffer routines and abort the parse.
Fix guththila_next_no_char to slide all the token to the next buffer, in the
case where the token starts well within the last buffer, i.e., start moving
at the lower of m_next and m_last_start, if set.
In the guththila_next_char routines, defer variable initialization to the
inner buffer handling where its needed.
Add svn:eol-style native to avoid CR issues with Windows.
